1
00:01:43,880 --> 00:01:44,600
I'm sorry.

2
00:01:44,840 --> 00:01:46,560
We did everything we could,

3
00:01:46,840 --> 00:01:48,480
but we couldn't save the baby.

4
00:01:57,080 --> 00:01:58,520
Then... then...

5
00:01:58,600 --> 00:02:00,240
My... my wife...

6
00:02:00,240 --> 00:02:01,480
and the other baby?

7
00:02:02,440 --> 00:02:03,160
They're all right.

8
00:02:03,840 --> 00:02:04,400
Don't worry.

9
00:02:05,200 --> 00:02:06,160
Xuemei is in recovery.

10
00:02:06,320 --> 00:02:06,960
The other baby

11
00:02:06,960 --> 00:02:07,840
is doing fine for now.

12
00:02:08,280 --> 00:02:08,880
The obstetricians

13
00:02:09,040 --> 00:02:10,200
will monitor them closely.

14
00:02:10,880 --> 00:02:11,240
Doctor,

15
00:02:11,520 --> 00:02:13,040
please, I'm begging you.

16
00:02:13,240 --> 00:02:14,520
Please protect my wife

17
00:02:14,520 --> 00:02:16,160
and... and the other baby.

18
00:02:17,120 --> 00:02:17,560
I will.

19
00:02:18,760 --> 00:02:19,240
Chief Xiaofeng.

20
00:02:19,840 --> 00:02:21,040
He Xuemei is having sudden, intense
contractions.

21
00:02:21,400 --> 00:02:21,920
She may be going into labor.

22
00:02:30,080 --> 00:02:31,640
Push down. Push down.

23
00:02:31,880 --> 00:02:32,640
Yes, that's it.

24
00:02:33,040 --> 00:02:33,400
Keep going.

25
00:02:33,720 --> 00:02:34,080
Yes.

26
00:02:34,480 --> 00:02:34,840
Good.

27
00:02:35,200 --> 00:02:35,840
Push. Push.

28
00:02:36,600 --> 00:02:37,800
Deep breaths. Deep breaths.

29
00:02:37,800 --> 00:02:38,720
Let's do it in one go. Come on.

30
00:02:39,200 --> 00:02:39,600
Push.

31
00:02:40,280 --> 00:02:41,520
Push downward. Downward.

32
00:02:42,040 --> 00:02:43,120
Yes. Don't lift your hips.

33
00:02:43,200 --> 00:02:43,800
Push downward.

34
00:02:44,760 --> 00:02:46,040
I can see the baby's hair.

35
00:02:46,320 --> 00:02:46,840
Xuemei.

36
00:03:01,800 --> 00:03:02,880
God, please protect her.

37
00:03:03,280 --> 00:03:04,200
God, please protect her.

38
00:03:04,240 --> 00:03:04,760
Xuemei.

39
00:03:05,040 --> 00:03:06,280
It's okay. It's okay.

40
00:03:11,160 --> 00:03:12,640
God, please protect her.

41
00:03:14,200 --> 00:03:14,640
Chief Pan

42
00:03:14,640 --> 00:03:16,240
is a very experienced obstetrician.

43
00:03:16,560 --> 00:03:17,520
And the other baby

44
00:03:17,600 --> 00:03:18,400
is healthy.

45
00:03:18,720 --> 00:03:19,800
Try not to worry too much.

46
00:03:21,800 --> 00:03:23,200
The baby's only six months along.

47
00:03:23,520 --> 00:03:24,720
If anything happens to Xuemei,

48
00:03:25,320 --> 00:03:25,720
I...

49
00:03:26,040 --> 00:03:27,120
I can't go on.

50
00:03:27,280 --> 00:03:29,120
I can't go on living.

51
00:03:34,200 --> 00:03:34,840
He Xuemei.

52
00:03:35,440 --> 00:03:36,200
You have to be brave.

53
00:03:36,800 --> 00:03:37,960
There is still a healthy baby.

54
00:03:38,040 --> 00:03:38,560
You must deliver him

55
00:03:38,640 --> 00:03:39,440
safely.

56
00:03:39,520 --> 00:03:40,080
Okay?

57
00:03:52,880 --> 00:03:53,840
Push downward.

58
00:03:54,400 --> 00:03:54,720
Yes.

59
00:03:54,960 --> 00:03:56,440
The baby's hair is showing.

60
00:03:56,600 --> 00:03:57,200
The hair is out.

61
00:03:57,400 --> 00:03:58,040
I can see it.

62
00:03:58,440 --> 00:03:58,880
Keep going.

63
00:03:59,640 --> 00:04:00,280
Good. That's it.

64
00:04:00,280 --> 00:04:01,040
Just like that.

65
00:04:01,440 --> 00:04:01,840
Keep going.

66
00:04:02,120 --> 00:04:02,480
Yes.

67
00:04:02,920 --> 00:04:03,280
Good.

68
00:04:03,560 --> 00:04:04,320
Push. Push.

69
00:04:23,120 --> 00:04:23,920
Family of He Xuemei?

70
00:04:24,840 --> 00:04:25,520
Mother and baby are safe.

71
00:04:29,200 --> 00:04:30,600
The baby weighs 700 grams.

72
00:04:31,720 --> 00:04:33,200
Because he was premature,

73
00:04:33,440 --> 00:04:33,880
we've already

74
00:04:33,880 --> 00:04:35,160
sent him to Neonatology.

75
00:04:38,240 --> 00:04:40,640
Can I see Xuemei?

76
00:04:41,440 --> 00:04:41,840
Come in.

77
00:04:42,160 --> 00:04:42,800
Okay. Okay.

78
00:05:01,440 --> 00:05:03,160
He Xuemei is stable now.

79
00:05:03,400 --> 00:05:04,160
Don't worry too much.

80
00:05:04,960 --> 00:05:06,200
She's given birth before,

81
00:05:06,320 --> 00:05:07,320
the premature baby is small,

82
00:05:07,600 --> 00:05:09,040
and it was a natural delivery,

83
00:05:09,400 --> 00:05:11,520
so she should recover quickly.

84
00:05:13,120 --> 00:05:14,520
Neonatology has experience

85
00:05:14,560 --> 00:05:15,280
caring for premature babies.

86
00:05:15,840 --> 00:05:17,600
Xuemei's baby will be fine too.

87
00:05:18,960 --> 00:05:20,400
You don't look well.

88
00:05:20,800 --> 00:05:22,320
Go rest in the lounge.

89
00:05:24,960 --> 00:05:26,280
Chief Pan and I can handle this.

90
00:05:27,920 --> 00:05:28,520
Professor Fang.

91
00:05:29,520 --> 00:05:30,720
Please go get some rest.

92
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,120
Xuemei.

93
00:05:38,720 --> 00:05:39,720
Dr. Fang is here.

94
00:05:40,600 --> 00:05:41,200
Dr. Fang.

95
00:05:44,840 --> 00:05:45,440
Xuemei.

96
00:05:45,880 --> 00:05:46,800
How are you feeling?

97
00:05:54,280 --> 00:05:55,320
I want to see her.

98
00:05:56,280 --> 00:05:56,840
Xuemei,

99
00:05:57,280 --> 00:05:58,160
don't worry.

100
00:05:58,560 --> 00:06:00,400
Your son is in Neonatology.

101
00:06:00,640 --> 00:06:01,440
Everything is normal.

102
00:06:02,800 --> 00:06:04,280
I want to see my daughter.

103
00:06:17,720 --> 00:06:18,840
I want to see her.

104
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:22,880
Please let me see her, okay?

105
00:06:31,240 --> 00:06:32,200
Please wait a moment.

106
00:06:34,520 --> 00:06:35,080
Chief Pan.

107
00:06:41,280 --> 00:06:41,840
Dr. Fang.

108
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:42,920
Chief Pan.

109
00:06:43,800 --> 00:06:44,400
I think

110
00:06:44,920 --> 00:06:45,840
she may need

111
00:06:45,840 --> 00:06:46,760
a proper goodbye.

112
00:06:49,960 --> 00:06:50,480
All right, then.

113
00:06:51,760 --> 00:06:52,760
If that's possible,

114
00:06:53,480 --> 00:06:54,920
the baby needs to be prepared too.

115
00:07:05,600 --> 00:07:06,640
Come on. Easy. Easy.

116
00:07:39,040 --> 00:07:40,480
Her hair is so dark.

117
00:07:40,520 --> 00:07:41,920
Just like Nini's.

118
00:07:45,120 --> 00:07:45,640
Xuemei.

119
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:47,600
Your sister's name is Mu Aini.

120
00:07:48,520 --> 00:07:48,840
You...

121
00:07:49,720 --> 00:07:51,040
your name is Mu Sini.

122
00:07:56,600 --> 00:07:57,760
Go find your sister.

123
00:07:59,840 --> 00:08:00,960
Keep each other company.

124
00:08:03,640 --> 00:08:05,280
I'm sorry, my baby.

125
00:08:14,800 --> 00:08:15,920
My Nini.

126
00:08:18,640 --> 00:08:19,200
Xuemei.

127
00:08:20,240 --> 00:08:21,200
All right. It's okay.

128
00:08:21,600 --> 00:08:22,720
Try to steady yourself.

129
00:08:23,080 --> 00:08:24,120
Don't grieve too hard.

130
00:08:24,640 --> 00:08:26,040
It's okay. It's okay.

131
00:08:45,880 --> 00:08:46,200
Mom.

132
00:08:47,800 --> 00:08:48,320
Thank you.

133
00:08:53,280 --> 00:08:54,600
We were so close.

134
00:08:56,960 --> 00:08:58,160
Just this close.

135
00:09:01,160 --> 00:09:02,560
I'd already placed the balloon.

136
00:09:08,720 --> 00:09:09,640
You did everything you could.

137
00:09:11,400 --> 00:09:12,160
Don't blame yourself too much.

138
00:09:12,240 --> 00:09:13,200
Of course I blame myself.

139
00:09:15,280 --> 00:09:16,160
And I'm worried.

140
00:09:16,600 --> 00:09:17,920
Xuemei, she...

141
00:09:23,800 --> 00:09:25,160
Xuemei has always been brave,

142
00:09:26,400 --> 00:09:26,960
and very strong.

143
00:09:28,800 --> 00:09:29,560
Later,

144
00:09:29,840 --> 00:09:31,200
we'll arrange counseling for her.

145
00:09:32,520 --> 00:09:33,520
I'll take good care of her.

146
00:09:34,040 --> 00:09:35,040
Don't worry too much.

147
00:09:45,600 --> 00:09:46,520
But what about you?

148
00:09:49,440 --> 00:09:50,120
What will you do?

149
00:09:52,480 --> 00:09:53,840
The balloon had no billing code.

150
00:09:56,800 --> 00:09:57,280
I know that.

151
00:09:57,280 --> 00:09:58,840
The balloon had no code.

152
00:09:59,960 --> 00:10:00,720
But at the time,

153
00:10:01,200 --> 00:10:02,720
the baby was about to lose fetal movement.

154
00:10:03,200 --> 00:10:04,480
We couldn't just stand by.

155
00:10:05,520 --> 00:10:06,080
I know.

156
00:10:10,920 --> 00:10:12,200
But without a code,

157
00:10:13,200 --> 00:10:13,880
the surgery has no

158
00:10:13,880 --> 00:10:15,200
procedural protection.

159
00:10:16,240 --> 00:10:17,400
When the appraisal committee

160
00:10:17,440 --> 00:10:18,640
rules on this case,

161
00:10:19,600 --> 00:10:20,560
you know what that means.

162
00:10:24,400 --> 00:10:25,640
Did Ouyang Da push you into this?

163
00:10:25,920 --> 00:10:26,400
No.

164
00:10:30,200 --> 00:10:31,240
Then it was because of me.

165
00:10:32,320 --> 00:10:33,560
Because I kept pressuring you,

166
00:10:33,720 --> 00:10:34,920
pushing you to operate on Xuemei.

167
00:10:35,440 --> 00:10:36,600
It had nothing to do with you.

168
00:10:38,480 --> 00:10:40,720
Sometimes it's a split-second decision.

169
00:10:41,920 --> 00:10:43,120
In that very moment,

170
00:10:43,120 --> 00:10:44,840
I decided to take the risk.

171
00:10:45,320 --> 00:10:46,880
For Xuemei and her daughter,

172
00:10:47,120 --> 00:10:48,320
and for myself.

173
00:10:48,440 --> 00:10:49,880
As long as the surgery succeeded,

174
00:10:50,800 --> 00:10:51,560
even if I was punished,

175
00:11:04,200 --> 00:11:05,280
I could bear it.

176
00:11:07,120 --> 00:11:07,840
Don't worry.

177
00:11:16,560 --> 00:11:17,240
Go on.

178
00:11:18,840 --> 00:11:19,280
Get back to work.

179
00:11:19,840 --> 00:11:20,320
Emergency call.

180
00:11:20,760 --> 00:11:21,560
Cardiology support needed.

181
00:11:25,920 --> 00:11:26,520
It's okay.

182
00:12:01,960 --> 00:12:02,520
What would you like?

183
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:14,200
A bottle of water.

184
00:12:19,840 --> 00:12:20,920
Twelve yuan. Scan here.

185
00:12:48,480 --> 00:12:49,520
There's no heartbeat.

186
00:14:04,520 --> 00:14:05,480
How could that happen?

187
00:14:34,480 --> 00:14:35,200
Didn't I tell you

188
00:14:35,200 --> 00:14:36,920
not to rush back early?

189
00:14:42,920 --> 00:14:43,960
How are things now?

190
00:14:45,200 --> 00:14:46,560
I went to Obstetrics this evening

191
00:14:46,560 --> 00:14:47,520
to see He Xuemei.

192
00:14:47,840 --> 00:14:49,480
She's still very weak,

193
00:14:49,560 --> 00:14:50,800
but mentally she's doing okay.

194
00:14:57,400 --> 00:14:57,960
What about Aunt Fang?

195
00:14:58,920 --> 00:15:00,200
She went home to rest.

196
00:15:01,600 --> 00:15:02,720
You didn't go stay with her?

197
00:15:04,720 --> 00:15:05,800
She wouldn't let me.

198
00:15:19,120 --> 00:15:20,840
Aunt Fang has been through so much.

199
00:15:21,240 --> 00:15:22,800
This setback is nothing to her.

200
00:15:24,120 --> 00:15:24,920
When life is on the line,

201
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:25,800
saving lives comes first.

202
00:15:26,840 --> 00:15:27,800
I support Aunt Fang.

203
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:28,960
I don't think she was wrong.

204
00:15:31,200 --> 00:15:31,880
Don't worry too much.

205
00:15:43,600 --> 00:15:44,400
Look.

206
00:15:44,880 --> 00:15:46,560
That surgery failed.

207
00:15:46,840 --> 00:15:48,200
The child is gone.

208
00:15:48,920 --> 00:15:49,920
I really don't understand.

209
00:15:50,120 --> 00:15:50,760
Among our medical school's

210
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:51,840
affiliated hospitals,

211
00:15:52,160 --> 00:15:53,280
Dongli is the strongest.

212
00:15:53,640 --> 00:15:54,440
And Professor Fang

213
00:15:54,560 --> 00:15:56,200
is practically legendary.

214
00:15:56,520 --> 00:15:58,040
How could she miss this time?

215
00:15:58,960 --> 00:16:00,080
They say that balloon

216
00:16:00,120 --> 00:16:01,600
had no code in Dongjiang.

217
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,800
It seems they used a non-compliant product.

218
00:16:05,400 --> 00:16:06,840
That mother must be devastated.

219
00:16:07,040 --> 00:16:08,520
Yes. It's terrifying.

220
00:16:08,960 --> 00:16:10,200
Have you seen this post?

221
00:16:10,280 --> 00:16:11,720
It says Dongli is holding an inquiry.

222
00:16:12,040 --> 00:16:13,520
They must be assigning responsibility.

223
00:16:14,560 --> 00:16:15,160
Now I finally know

224
00:16:15,160 --> 00:16:16,320
what it means to be unable to defend yourself.

225
00:16:16,840 --> 00:16:18,120
They're actually saying we were

226
00:16:18,120 --> 00:16:19,120
doing rare-disease surgery

227
00:16:19,200 --> 00:16:20,200
and using patients as guinea pigs.

228
00:16:20,520 --> 00:16:21,880
That's absolutely absurd.

229
00:16:22,840 --> 00:16:24,600
What people are saying online is outrageous.

230
00:16:25,200 --> 00:16:26,640
They say the whole congenital heart project

231
00:16:26,720 --> 00:16:27,520
is a scam.

232
00:16:27,880 --> 00:16:28,520
They even say there are

233
00:16:28,600 --> 00:16:29,800
shady secrets behind it.

234
00:16:30,800 --> 00:16:31,840
What secrets?

235
00:16:32,200 --> 00:16:33,520
We brought them all the way to Dongjiang.

236
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:34,560
Are we trafficking women and children now?

237
00:16:35,640 --> 00:16:37,040
The hospital office just informed me too.

238
00:16:37,800 --> 00:16:39,240
Tomorrow's ethics meeting has been upgraded.

239
00:16:39,800 --> 00:16:40,760
The health supervision department will lead it,

240
00:16:40,920 --> 00:16:42,400
with third-party experts

241
00:16:42,840 --> 00:16:44,080
forming an investigation panel.

242
00:16:44,920 --> 00:16:45,840
For He Xuemei's case,

243
00:16:46,560 --> 00:16:47,560
they'll hold a formal inquiry.

244
00:16:49,200 --> 00:16:49,960
Why does this feel like

245
00:16:50,040 --> 00:16:51,160
it's getting more and more serious?

246
00:16:51,840 --> 00:16:53,280
Mom hasn't slept well these past two days.

247
00:16:54,560 --> 00:16:55,720
You're the congenital heart project

248
00:16:55,720 --> 00:16:56,320
lead.

249
00:16:56,520 --> 00:16:57,440
You'll have to speak too, right?

250
00:16:58,720 --> 00:16:59,400
All right.

251
00:16:59,960 --> 00:17:00,920
Just tell the truth.

252
00:17:01,240 --> 00:17:02,560
Say the patient's wishes were clear,

253
00:17:02,640 --> 00:17:03,720
that she strongly requested intrauterine
intervention.

254
00:17:04,040 --> 00:17:05,200
Lay everything out honestly.

255
00:17:05,320 --> 00:17:06,400
Aunt Fang will be fine.

256
00:17:07,520 --> 00:17:09,160
Brother, we're counting on you.

257
00:17:10,760 --> 00:17:11,760
You should be there too, right?

258
00:17:12,120 --> 00:17:13,040
Of course I'm going.

259
00:17:13,960 --> 00:17:14,480
That's even better.

260
00:17:14,600 --> 00:17:15,400
The three of us will go together.

261
00:17:15,560 --> 00:17:15,920
Hello?

262
00:17:16,840 --> 00:17:17,280
What?

263
00:17:17,720 --> 00:17:18,480
I'll be right there.

264
00:17:19,520 --> 00:17:20,200
What happened?

265
00:17:21,640 --> 00:17:22,720
Don't stop me.

266
00:17:23,160 --> 00:17:24,200
You've gone too far.

267
00:17:24,200 --> 00:17:24,840
Do you know that?

268
00:17:25,520 --> 00:17:26,200
If we'd known this would happen,

269
00:17:26,240 --> 00:17:27,520
we would've reduced the pregnancy.

270
00:17:27,800 --> 00:17:29,320
You were testing some new product,

271
00:17:29,440 --> 00:17:30,560
messing with some new technology.

272
00:17:30,840 --> 00:17:31,840
Who gave you the right to use my child

273
00:17:31,920 --> 00:17:32,520
as an experiment?

274
00:17:32,720 --> 00:17:34,640
You've bullied us too much.

275
00:17:34,880 --> 00:17:35,320
Please, calm down.

276
00:17:35,320 --> 00:17:35,600
Don't touch me.

277
00:17:35,600 --> 00:17:36,200
Calm down.

278
00:17:36,440 --> 00:17:37,280
This is a hospital.

279
00:17:37,920 --> 00:17:39,040
People online don't know the facts.

280
00:17:39,440 --> 00:17:40,640
You can't listen to their nonsense.

281
00:17:41,080 --> 00:17:42,400
Who is talking nonsense?

282
00:17:42,960 --> 00:17:44,800
My child is gone.

283
00:17:45,640 --> 00:17:46,400
I'm not talking to you.

284
00:17:46,720 --> 00:17:47,400
I want Zhou Xiaofeng.

285
00:17:47,640 --> 00:17:48,280
I want Fang Zhuqing.

286
00:17:49,040 --> 00:17:50,760
I'm calling the police.

287
00:17:51,720 --> 00:17:52,040
Move aside.

288
00:17:52,120 --> 00:17:52,720
Don't touch me.

289
00:17:52,720 --> 00:17:53,240
Zhou Xiaofeng!

290
00:17:53,240 --> 00:17:54,040
Don't touch me.

291
00:17:54,440 --> 00:17:54,920
Don't touch me.

292
00:17:55,160 --> 00:17:55,600
What are you doing?

293
00:17:56,040 --> 00:17:56,880
What do you think I'm doing?

294
00:17:58,520 --> 00:17:59,520
That balloon you used

295
00:17:59,520 --> 00:18:01,120
on my child,

296
